# verasic-git-commits

Hard convention for **every commit** (any branch, any agent, any IDE). The
full spec and recipes live in `.cursor/skills/verasic-git-commits/references/`
— read `commit-protocol.md` before your first commit of a session. If that
folder is missing, the installation is broken: say so and fall back to the
digest below.

## Non-negotiables (digest)

- subject: `type: summary` or `type(scope): summary` — types: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `style`, `perf`, `build`, `ci`, `revert`; **lowercase** summary start, imperative mood, no trailing period
- body (optional; blank line after subject): lowercase first sentence; explain **why**, not a file list; multiple items = `- ` list, one item per line
- casing: lowercase first sentence, natural casing for proper nouns/acronyms/components (`User ID`, `PROJ-1234`, `TabOverview`); backtick technical literals (`--set`, `git commit`, `src/foo.ts`, `TAG_NAME`)
- never: `Co-authored-by:` trailers in **any casing**, `Generated with ...` lines, decorative emoji in subject
- never: AI-session language — tool/model names, agent/orchestration vocabulary, plan-step references, chat narration, assistant voice (`I added`, `let me`, `this commit`); write as a teammate explaining why — full pattern tables + allowlist in `references/conventions.md`
- never: `--no-verify` / `-n` on `git commit` — hooks are the enforcement floor, not an obstacle; if a hook rejects the message, fix the message
- multi-line messages: HEREDOC so casing stays intentional

## After every commit — verify

```bash
git log -1 --format=%B | grep -qiE '^co-authored-by:' && echo 'TRAILER PRESENT' || echo 'clean'
```

- **clean** → done
- **TRAILER PRESENT** + not pushed → use the `git commit-tree` escape hatch in `references/commit-protocol.md`; **do not** loop on `--amend` (the wrapper re-injects)
- already pushed → no force-push; report and fix on a follow-up with approval

Repos with the verasic `commit-msg` hook wired (lefthook or `core.hooksPath`)
strip trailers automatically and reject mechanical style violations — verify
stays as the cheap proof.

## Pre-push audit

Run `/verasic-audit-commits` before the first push of a branch or opening a PR
— audit-only by default.
